Notes
-----

CMS elements (`www.element`):

- The `model` field is filtered dynamically to only show Tryton models that
  behave as Voyager components (instances of `trytond.modules.voyager.voyager.Component`).
- Preview visibility can be toggled per element with `show_preview` (default: True).
  The preview is also hidden when the element is not linked to a page.
- Preview schema placeholders normalize relational fields:
  `Many2One` values are represented as `None` and `One2Many` as an empty list `[]`.
- Site rendering now explicitly adds header/footer tags to the DOM container to
  preserve the intended order (header above content, footer below).
